## 6. Critical User Flows: Success Metrics

### Primary Success Metric: Time to First Message

**Target**: <15 minutes from signup

**Measurement points**:

1. Account created â†’ timestamp
2. First job qualified â†’ timestamp
3. First company created â†’ timestamp
4. First message sent â†’ timestamp

**Funnel**:

```
100% â†’ Sign up
 90% â†’ Qualify first job (10% drop-off)
 80% â†’ Find decision makers (10% drop-off)
 65% â†’ Send first message (15% drop-off)
```

**Goal**: Minimize drop-off at each stage

---

### Secondary Metrics

**Engagement (Daily Active Users)**:

- Dashboard visit
- Jobs viewed
- Companies researched
- Messages sent

**Target behaviors**:

- 3-5 jobs qualified per day
- 2-3 companies researched per day
- 5-10 messages sent per week
- 1-2 responses per week

**Retention triggers**:

- Response received (highest retention driver)
- Meeting scheduled (conversion event)
- Client won (ultimate success)

---

## 7. Edge Cases & Error States

### Error Flow A: No Decision Makers Found

```
User clicks "Find Decision Makers"
â†’ System searches LinkedIn
â†’ No results found

Show message:
"We couldn't find decision makers automatically.
You can:
- Add contacts manually
- Try again later (we're improving our search)
- Skip for now and come back"

[Add Manually] [Try Again] [Skip]
```

---

### Error Flow B: Duplicate Company

```
User tries to qualify job
â†’ System detects company already in pipeline

Show modal:
"This company is already in your pipeline!
Status: Outreach Started
Last activity: 3 days ago

[View Company] [Qualify Anyway as Separate Job]"
```

---

### Error Flow C: Email Sending Fails

```
User sends message via Gmail
â†’ Gmail API error (rate limit, auth expired)

Show error:
"Message couldn't be sent.
Reason: Gmail rate limit reached

What to do:
- Copy message to clipboard and send manually
- Try again in 1 hour
- Check Gmail connection in Settings"

[Copy Message] [Try Again] [Settings]
```

---

## 8. Mobile User Flow (Simplified)

**Philosophy**: Mobile is for checking and light actions, not deep work

### Mobile Priority Flows

**Check notifications** (30 seconds):

```
1. Open app
2. Dashboard shows:
   - "3 new responses"
   - "5 follow-ups due today"
3. Tap notification â†’ View response
4. Quick reply or mark for desktop follow-up
```

**Quick job qualification** (1-2 minutes):

```
1. Jobs tab â†’ New
2. Swipe through jobs (Tinder-style)
3. Swipe right = Qualify
4. Swipe left = Skip
5. Job qualified â†’ Toast: "Added to pipeline"
```

**Review company** (read-only):

```
1. Companies tab
2. Tap company â†’ Full screen view
3. Scroll through:
   - Company info
   - Decision makers
   - Recent activity
4. Can mark favorites, add notes
5. Deep actions (messaging) â†’ "Continue on desktop"
```

**Mobile = Triage, Desktop = Deep Work**

---

## 9. User Flow Best Practices Summary

### Do's:

âœ… Start the onboarding process immediately after someone engages with your brand - send welcome email right after signup to bring people into the fold early

âœ… Help users do the thing fast - identify their "aha moment" and streamline your flow to help them achieve it as quickly as possible

âœ… Help customers understand how your product helps them at every touchpoint - retention possibility increases significantly when you treat customer interactions as a holistic experience

âœ… Progressive disclosure: Show complexity gradually

âœ… Celebrate wins: Toast notifications for completed actions

âœ… Clear CTAs: Always show next step

âœ… Minimal clicks: 3 clicks to any action

âœ… Escape hatches: Always allow "Skip" or "Do Later"

### Don'ts:

âŒ Don't force linear onboarding (let users explore)

âŒ Don't hide key features behind menus

âŒ Don't require too much info upfront

âŒ Don't make users read long instructions

âŒ Don't auto-play videos or modals that block content

âŒ Don't have dead ends (always show next action)

---

## 10. Recommended Implementation Priority

### Week 1: Core Happy Path

- [ ] Job qualification workflow
- [ ] Company creation flow
- [ ] Decision maker display
- [ ] Basic message generation
- [ ] Send/copy message

### Week 2: Enhanced Navigation

- [ ] Dashboard with action items
- [ ] Global search
- [ ] Filter persistence
- [ ] Breadcrumbs
- [ ] Quick actions on hover

### Week 3: Onboarding Polish

- [ ] First-time user tooltips
- [ ] Interactive tour
- [ ] Empty states with guidance
- [ ] Success celebrations
- [ ] Help documentation

### Week 4: Power User Features

- [ ] Bulk actions
- [ ] Keyboard shortcuts
- [ ] Saved filters
- [ ] Custom views
- [ ] Advanced search

---

## Final Recommendation

Your **primary user flow should be**:

```
Jobs Feed (discover)
  â†“
Qualify interesting jobs
  â†“
Companies page (review pipeline)
  â†“
Company Detail (research)
  â†“
Find Decision Makers
  â†“
Generate & Send Messages
  â†“
Conversations (track responses)
  â†“
[LOOP: Follow up or qualify more jobs]
```

**This should take**:

- First time: 15 minutes
- Daily routine: 15-20 minutes
- Weekly deep work: 1-2 hours

**Make this flow effortless**, and your users will love you.
